### Supabase Configuration (Required)
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard: Settings → API
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

### Server Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000

### Database Configuration (for migrations)
# If you're using Supabase Postgres, get connection string from: Settings → Database
PGHOST=db.yourproject.supabase.co
PGPORT=5432
PGDATABASE=postgres
PGUSER=postgres
PGPASSWORD=your-postgres-password

### Storage Configuration
SUPABASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=images

### Frontend Configuration
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3001
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGIN=*

### Important Security Notes:
# - SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: Safe for client-side use (public key with RLS protection)
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: Server-only, bypasses RLS, NEVER expose to client
# - In production, use your hosting provider's secret manager for sensitive keys
# - Never commit the actual .env file to version control
